WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.650 align:middle line:90%


00:00:07.650 --> 00:00:11.280 align:middle line:84%
>> Close to a clearing in the
middle of a field at the peak

00:00:11.280 --> 00:00:14.790 align:middle line:84%
of a hill or on the slopes of a
health stand stone giants which

00:00:14.790 --> 00:00:17.080 align:middle line:84%
have stood for
thousands of years.

00:00:17.080 --> 00:00:19.185 align:middle line:84%
They mark the landscape
with a mysterious trace.

00:00:19.185 --> 00:00:32.530 align:middle line:90%


00:00:32.530 --> 00:00:35.540 align:middle line:84%
Grazing giant stones has
been a part of many cultures

00:00:35.540 --> 00:00:37.530 align:middle line:90%
around the world.

00:00:37.530 --> 00:00:40.640 align:middle line:84%
However, the most spectacular
and the most ancient forms

00:00:40.640 --> 00:00:42.770 align:middle line:84%
are found on the
French Atlantic coast

00:00:42.770 --> 00:00:45.190 align:middle line:90%
and in the United Kingdom.

00:00:45.190 --> 00:00:47.020 align:middle line:84%
These imposing
stone blocks called

00:00:47.020 --> 00:00:49.300 align:middle line:84%
megaliths, from
Greek megas meaning

00:00:49.300 --> 00:00:53.220 align:middle line:84%
great and lithos meaning
stone, raise many questions.

00:00:53.220 --> 00:00:56.000 align:middle line:84%
Some people think
they are monuments.

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:57.690 align:middle line:84%
>> If this stone was
raised for someone,

00:00:57.690 --> 00:00:59.520 align:middle line:90%
they must have been important.

00:00:59.520 --> 00:01:02.190 align:middle line:84%
>> Others ask what force
can have raised them.

00:01:02.190 --> 00:01:05.209 align:middle line:84%
>> Could it be that our
ancient ancestors somehow knew

00:01:05.209 --> 00:01:08.975 align:middle line:84%
and manipulated
frequency of levitation?

00:01:08.975 --> 00:01:13.690 align:middle line:84%
>> Are these constructions the
work of architects or artists?

00:01:13.690 --> 00:01:16.440 align:middle line:84%
>> We ask if it was the same
hand that carved all these

00:01:16.440 --> 00:01:17.520 align:middle line:90%
rocks.

00:01:17.520 --> 00:01:19.410 align:middle line:10%
In which case, the
artist would be

00:01:19.410 --> 00:01:22.595 align:middle line:10%
the Michelangelo of their time.

00:01:22.595 --> 00:01:26.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Are the megaliths
vestiges of ancient beliefs?

00:01:26.240 --> 00:01:30.180 align:middle line:84%
>> It's obvious that the stones
are laid out in some form

00:01:30.180 --> 00:01:35.560 align:middle line:84%
of astrological, cosmic
thinking behind them.

00:01:35.560 --> 00:01:37.690 align:middle line:84%
>> Surrounded by
mystery and legend,

00:01:37.690 --> 00:01:40.630 align:middle line:84%
the megaliths attract
scientists, artists,

00:01:40.630 --> 00:01:43.354 align:middle line:84%
adventurers, and
followers from everywhere.

00:01:43.354 --> 00:01:53.700 align:middle line:90%


00:01:53.700 --> 00:01:55.860 align:middle line:84%
For centuries,
mankind has wondered

00:01:55.860 --> 00:01:57.750 align:middle line:84%
about the origins
and significance

00:01:57.750 --> 00:01:59.640 align:middle line:90%
of these strange monuments.

00:01:59.640 --> 00:02:02.160 align:middle line:84%
In the Middle Ages, they were
seen as the work of the devil

00:02:02.160 --> 00:02:06.220 align:middle line:84%
or of giants who lived on the
earth before the Great Flood.

00:02:06.220 --> 00:02:09.880 align:middle line:84%
Later, they were attributed to
the druids, Celtic priests who

00:02:09.880 --> 00:02:12.880 align:middle line:84%
raised them in order to
celebrate their rituals.

00:02:12.880 --> 00:02:15.160 align:middle line:84%
Those with a fertile
imagination connect them

00:02:15.160 --> 00:02:19.510 align:middle line:84%
with supernatural forces or
extraterrestrial visitors.

00:02:19.510 --> 00:02:21.320 align:middle line:84%
Whatever the
theories put forward,

00:02:21.320 --> 00:02:23.260 align:middle line:84%
they always raise
the same questions--

00:02:23.260 --> 00:02:28.320 align:middle line:84%
who raised these monuments,
when, how, and why?

00:02:28.320 --> 00:02:30.360 align:middle line:10%
These questions will
come up during our voyage

00:02:30.360 --> 00:02:32.723 align:middle line:10%
to some iconic signs
from the west of France

00:02:32.723 --> 00:02:33.931 align:middle line:10%
to the far north of Scotland.

00:02:33.931 --> 00:02:38.490 align:middle line:90%


00:02:38.490 --> 00:02:39.820 align:middle line:90%
Carnac is our first stop.

00:02:39.820 --> 00:02:43.080 align:middle line:90%


00:02:43.080 --> 00:02:45.270 align:middle line:84%
The menhir, long
stones in Celtic,

00:02:45.270 --> 00:02:46.780 align:middle line:84%
are arranged in
impressive lines.

00:02:46.780 --> 00:02:49.640 align:middle line:90%


00:02:49.640 --> 00:02:51.530 align:middle line:84%
The site is unique in
the world, for there

00:02:51.530 --> 00:02:53.730 align:middle line:84%
are more than 3,000
stones aligned

00:02:53.730 --> 00:02:56.150 align:middle line:90%
over nearly 4 kilometers.

00:02:56.150 --> 00:02:57.890 align:middle line:84%
The age of the site
has been estimated

00:02:57.890 --> 00:03:01.766 align:middle line:84%
to be 4,000 years BC, thanks
to carbon-14 dating of charcoal

00:03:01.766 --> 00:03:03.140 align:middle line:84%
found at the base
of some menhir.

00:03:03.140 --> 00:03:06.297 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:03:06.297 --> 00:03:08.220 align:middle line:84%
At first site, the
groups are just

00:03:08.220 --> 00:03:11.700 align:middle line:84%
alignments of uncut stones,
but to a careful observer,

00:03:11.700 --> 00:03:13.965 align:middle line:84%
the arrangement is a lot
more complex than it seems.

00:03:13.965 --> 00:03:17.390 align:middle line:90%


00:03:17.390 --> 00:03:19.730 align:middle line:10%
>> When you progress
along these alignments,

00:03:19.730 --> 00:03:22.280 align:middle line:10%
there's a surprising
effect of perspective.

00:03:22.280 --> 00:03:24.880 align:middle line:10%
There's this gentle slope,
and at the same time,

00:03:24.880 --> 00:03:26.930 align:middle line:10%
the small hill, which
is really emphasized

00:03:26.930 --> 00:03:32.395 align:middle line:10%
by the size of the monoliths,
which get bigger and bigger.

00:03:32.395 --> 00:03:34.640 align:middle line:84%
But there's more
to it than that.

00:03:34.640 --> 00:03:38.030 align:middle line:84%
Some studies have shown that
these quarried stones here

00:03:38.030 --> 00:03:41.566 align:middle line:84%
often have an outcropped
side and a quarried side,

00:03:41.566 --> 00:03:43.940 align:middle line:84%
which means that all this
granite emerged from the ground

00:03:43.940 --> 00:03:45.760 align:middle line:90%
and was extracted from the site.

00:03:45.760 --> 00:03:48.710 align:middle line:90%


00:03:48.710 --> 00:03:51.260 align:middle line:84%
And there are groups of
rows like that where there

00:03:51.260 --> 00:03:54.860 align:middle line:84%
are two lines of dressed stones,
and the sides which were cut,

00:03:54.860 --> 00:03:57.200 align:middle line:84%
which are flatter, are
all turned inwards.

00:03:57.200 --> 00:04:00.520 align:middle line:90%


00:04:00.520 --> 00:04:02.990 align:middle line:84%
I mean to say it's an
arrangement which is planned.

00:04:02.990 --> 00:04:05.240 align:middle line:90%
It hasn't happened by chance.

00:04:05.240 --> 00:04:08.240 align:middle line:84%
If that allows a particular
pathway or a kind

00:04:08.240 --> 00:04:10.850 align:middle line:84%
of precession, it's
difficult to imagine,

00:04:10.850 --> 00:04:13.838 align:middle line:90%
but it's very possible.

00:04:13.838 --> 00:04:17.170 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:17.170 --> 00:04:22.620 align:middle line:90%


00:04:22.620 --> 00:04:24.860 align:middle line:84%
Whether there was an
architect to manage the work

00:04:24.860 --> 00:04:26.610 align:middle line:90%
is very hard to tell.

00:04:26.610 --> 00:04:28.230 align:middle line:84%
There were surely
very, very strong

00:04:28.230 --> 00:04:30.810 align:middle line:84%
symbolic and social
contexts, but I

00:04:30.810 --> 00:04:34.724 align:middle line:84%
think we're far from
having all the answers.

00:04:34.724 --> 00:04:37.628 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:37.628 --> 00:04:45.630 align:middle line:90%


00:04:45.630 --> 00:04:49.170 align:middle line:84%
When it comes to the orientation
of the rows, when we analyze

00:04:49.170 --> 00:04:51.360 align:middle line:84%
a lot of these, we
can see that there

00:04:51.360 --> 00:04:53.370 align:middle line:84%
are very few or none
which correspond

00:04:53.370 --> 00:04:56.580 align:middle line:84%
to any special
astronomical axis.

00:04:56.580 --> 00:04:59.010 align:middle line:84%
There's no alignment
truly oriented

00:04:59.010 --> 00:05:03.510 align:middle line:84%
towards the rising of the
sun, solstice, or lunar axes.

00:05:03.510 --> 00:05:06.840 align:middle line:84%
The principle behind this, and
the concept of emplacement,

00:05:06.840 --> 00:05:09.710 align:middle line:90%
is something else entirely.

00:05:09.710 --> 00:05:12.995 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:12.995 --> 00:05:15.450 align:middle line:90%


00:05:15.450 --> 00:05:17.790 align:middle line:84%
>> The logic behind the
emplacement of menhir in this

00:05:17.790 --> 00:05:20.500 align:middle line:84%
landscape is the subject
which Christian Obeltz,

00:05:20.500 --> 00:05:23.460 align:middle line:84%
a self-educated
archeologist, is exploring.

00:05:23.460 --> 00:05:25.770 align:middle line:84%
Christian has been traveling
the Brittany landscape

00:05:25.770 --> 00:05:28.050 align:middle line:84%
for 25 years,
trying to understand

00:05:28.050 --> 00:05:33.000 align:middle line:84%
the geographical placement
of these alignments.

00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:36.000 align:middle line:84%
The site of Kerzerho, a
few kilometers from Carnac,

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:39.600 align:middle line:90%
is one of his favorite stops.

00:05:39.600 --> 00:05:42.100 align:middle line:10%
>> I'll show you the plan
made by the English geometrist

00:05:42.100 --> 00:05:44.290 align:middle line:10%
Murray Vicars in 1832.

00:05:44.290 --> 00:05:45.780 align:middle line:84%
He was a great
geometrist who was

00:05:45.780 --> 00:05:47.430 align:middle line:90%
working for the English crown.

00:05:47.430 --> 00:05:50.590 align:middle line:84%
So here's what he saw
when he came in 1832--

00:05:50.590 --> 00:05:52.110 align:middle line:90%
the alignment where we are.

00:05:52.110 --> 00:05:54.540 align:middle line:84%
There's two kilometers
100 meters from one

00:05:54.540 --> 00:05:56.190 align:middle line:84%
end to the other
of the alignment.

00:05:56.190 --> 00:05:57.960 align:middle line:84%
It's the largest group
of standing stones

00:05:57.960 --> 00:05:59.020 align:middle line:90%
known in Europe.

00:05:59.020 --> 00:06:01.520 align:middle line:84%
What's the most surprising is
that the lines aren't straight

00:06:01.520 --> 00:06:03.270 align:middle line:90%
at all, and people say, why?

00:06:03.270 --> 00:06:05.970 align:middle line:84%
The relief justifies the
changes of direction.

00:06:05.970 --> 00:06:08.520 align:middle line:84%
For example, here you see
that the lines of menhir

00:06:08.520 --> 00:06:10.320 align:middle line:84%
are all going in
the same direction.

00:06:10.320 --> 00:06:13.190 align:middle line:84%
And when you come to this path,
which is just beside a stream,

00:06:13.190 --> 00:06:14.970 align:middle line:90%
there's a change of direction.

00:06:14.970 --> 00:06:18.870 align:middle line:84%
Then the lines will bend and
reach up to this rocky ridge.

00:06:18.870 --> 00:06:21.180 align:middle line:84%
Every change of direction
corresponds with the line

00:06:21.180 --> 00:06:23.230 align:middle line:90%
to a hill or water.

00:06:23.230 --> 00:06:26.681 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:26.681 --> 00:06:27.670 align:middle line:90%


00:06:27.670 --> 00:06:30.250 align:middle line:84%
>> The inclusion of the menhir
in their natural surroundings

00:06:30.250 --> 00:06:32.740 align:middle line:84%
seems to have been a major
concern of our ancestor

00:06:32.740 --> 00:06:34.070 align:middle line:90%
builders.

00:06:34.070 --> 00:06:35.920 align:middle line:84%
They were doubtless
led by aesthetic logic,

00:06:35.920 --> 00:06:37.990 align:middle line:90%
but also by a symbolic quality.

00:06:37.990 --> 00:06:41.150 align:middle line:90%


00:06:41.150 --> 00:06:43.430 align:middle line:84%
It's true that these lines
of stone stretching out

00:06:43.430 --> 00:06:47.880 align:middle line:84%
through the landscape
are impressive.

00:06:47.880 --> 00:06:49.900 align:middle line:84%
>> It's a symbol of the
power of these people.

00:06:49.900 --> 00:06:51.860 align:middle line:84%
There's really the
idea that the territory

00:06:51.860 --> 00:06:54.310 align:middle line:90%
is barred off by something.

00:06:54.310 --> 00:06:56.540 align:middle line:84%
It's the symbol of an
ethnic group belonging

00:06:56.540 --> 00:06:59.240 align:middle line:84%
to a great family,
a large community

00:06:59.240 --> 00:07:00.890 align:middle line:84%
with a common culture,
which does this.

00:07:00.890 --> 00:07:05.690 align:middle line:90%


00:07:05.690 --> 00:07:08.090 align:middle line:84%
>> However, a major
question remains.

00:07:08.090 --> 00:07:10.120 align:middle line:84%
Why were these
monumental groups raised?

00:07:10.120 --> 00:07:12.760 align:middle line:90%


00:07:12.760 --> 00:07:16.630 align:middle line:84%
Commemorative stones for people
or events, ceremonial places,

00:07:16.630 --> 00:07:17.930 align:middle line:90%
territory markers--

00:07:17.930 --> 00:07:20.000 align:middle line:84%
there are many
hypotheses, but the answer

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:22.630 align:middle line:84%
lies forever buried with
the minds of our ancestors.

00:07:22.630 --> 00:07:25.190 align:middle line:90%


00:07:25.190 --> 00:07:28.720 align:middle line:84%
>> It has to be said that about
everything concerning the daily

00:07:28.720 --> 00:07:32.050 align:middle line:84%
life of these people,
their dwellings,

00:07:32.050 --> 00:07:35.340 align:middle line:90%
very little data is available.

00:07:35.340 --> 00:07:37.150 align:middle line:84%
There have been
a few excavations

00:07:37.150 --> 00:07:39.520 align:middle line:90%
made of the habitations.

00:07:39.520 --> 00:07:43.162 align:middle line:84%
I think we're missing
a great many elements.

00:07:43.162 --> 00:07:46.459 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:46.459 --> 00:07:49.760 align:middle line:90%


00:07:49.760 --> 00:07:51.830 align:middle line:84%
>> The megaliths are an
illustration of the great

00:07:51.830 --> 00:07:56.150 align:middle line:84%
change in human history between
6,000 and 2,000 years BC.

00:07:56.150 --> 00:07:58.270 align:middle line:84%
This period is known
as the Neolithic,

00:07:58.270 --> 00:08:00.620 align:middle line:84%
and is the time when our
hunter-gatherer ancestors

00:08:00.620 --> 00:08:04.142 align:middle line:84%
became sedentary, invented
agriculture, animal farming,

00:08:04.142 --> 00:08:05.600 align:middle line:84%
and built tombs to
bury their dead.

00:08:05.600 --> 00:08:08.490 align:middle line:90%


00:08:08.490 --> 00:08:10.680 align:middle line:84%
Their collective
tombs, called dolmen,

00:08:10.680 --> 00:08:13.380 align:middle line:84%
appeared at the same
period as the menhir.

00:08:13.380 --> 00:08:14.970 align:middle line:84%
They are built of
a horizontal slab

00:08:14.970 --> 00:08:17.470 align:middle line:84%
of stone posed on vertical
stones which hold it up.

00:08:17.470 --> 00:08:22.210 align:middle line:90%


00:08:22.210 --> 00:08:26.230 align:middle line:84%
>> The humans of the Neolithic
went inside this corridor

00:08:26.230 --> 00:08:28.630 align:middle line:90%
and placed bodies all along it.

00:08:28.630 --> 00:08:32.320 align:middle line:84%
We know there could be more than
10, up to 100 bodies inside.

00:08:32.320 --> 00:08:35.556 align:middle line:90%


00:08:35.556 --> 00:08:38.620 align:middle line:84%
>> Dolmen, like menhir,
bear witness to the birth

00:08:38.620 --> 00:08:41.230 align:middle line:90%
of a culture 6,000 years ago.

00:08:41.230 --> 00:08:43.092 align:middle line:84%
>> It's really the start
of our own culture,

00:08:43.092 --> 00:08:45.550 align:middle line:84%
because it's the first time in
the history of humanity that

00:08:45.550 --> 00:08:47.995 align:middle line:84%
people made something which
was not just made for survival

00:08:47.995 --> 00:08:48.795 align:middle line:90%
purposes.

00:08:48.795 --> 00:08:51.350 align:middle line:90%


00:08:51.350 --> 00:08:54.984 align:middle line:84%
>> But how did people manage
in 4,000 BC to extract these

00:08:54.984 --> 00:08:56.025 align:middle line:90%
enormous blocks of stone?

00:08:56.025 --> 00:09:00.330 align:middle line:90%


00:09:00.330 --> 00:09:02.850 align:middle line:84%
>> The Neolithic people
worked at the fissures,

00:09:02.850 --> 00:09:04.680 align:middle line:90%
making little notches.

00:09:04.680 --> 00:09:06.960 align:middle line:84%
They just had to put
bits of wood into these

00:09:06.960 --> 00:09:08.790 align:middle line:84%
and then soak them
in water for the wood

00:09:08.790 --> 00:09:12.980 align:middle line:84%
to swell and finally crack
open the rock a little more.

00:09:12.980 --> 00:09:15.450 align:middle line:84%
And there, that's really
the face they cracked.

00:09:15.450 --> 00:09:17.950 align:middle line:84%
As well as that,
it's a typical case.

00:09:17.950 --> 00:09:21.000 align:middle line:84%
There are extraction
notches on either side.

00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:24.280 align:middle line:84%
There are two notches
here and two there.

00:09:24.280 --> 00:09:27.500 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:09:27.500 --> 00:09:28.420 align:middle line:90%


00:09:28.420 --> 00:09:29.980 align:middle line:84%
While the raising
of these stones

00:09:29.980 --> 00:09:32.440 align:middle line:84%
must have happened during
great gatherings of people,

00:09:32.440 --> 00:09:34.060 align:middle line:84%
the sheer number
put in place must

00:09:34.060 --> 00:09:35.410 align:middle line:90%
have taken hundreds of years.

00:09:35.410 --> 00:09:38.060 align:middle line:90%


00:09:38.060 --> 00:09:40.400 align:middle line:84%
The sight of these
thousands of standing stones

00:09:40.400 --> 00:09:42.230 align:middle line:90%
raises an immediate question.

00:09:42.230 --> 00:09:47.060 align:middle line:84%
Why are they concentrated at
Carnac and the area around it?

00:09:47.060 --> 00:09:50.320 align:middle line:84%
>> There must have been
a very dense population,

00:09:50.320 --> 00:09:53.350 align:middle line:84%
or otherwise a place where
gatherings were inevitable,

00:09:53.350 --> 00:09:56.530 align:middle line:84%
to raise these cut stones
and gigantic monuments.

00:09:56.530 --> 00:10:03.390 align:middle line:90%


00:10:03.390 --> 00:10:07.410 align:middle line:84%
>> In 4,000 BC, was the Brittany
coast a kind of El Dorado

00:10:07.410 --> 00:10:08.880 align:middle line:90%
attracting a dense population?

00:10:08.880 --> 00:10:12.240 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:10:12.240 --> 00:10:13.680 align:middle line:90%


00:10:13.680 --> 00:10:16.130 align:middle line:84%
>> In the Neolithic, they
had everything here--

00:10:16.130 --> 00:10:19.370 align:middle line:84%
excellent land, the sea,
cultural and business exchanges

00:10:19.370 --> 00:10:20.230 align:middle line:90%
by boat.

00:10:20.230 --> 00:10:21.950 align:middle line:84%
And it's probable that
the making of salt

00:10:21.950 --> 00:10:24.890 align:middle line:84%
was the reason for the
region being so rich.

00:10:24.890 --> 00:10:27.890 align:middle line:84%
You can see that it's the sea's
edge that is literally bordered

00:10:27.890 --> 00:10:29.570 align:middle line:84%
with these pillars,
and by looking

00:10:29.570 --> 00:10:31.370 align:middle line:84%
at the Carnac alignments,
you can really

00:10:31.370 --> 00:10:33.470 align:middle line:84%
see their idea of
a barrier of stones

00:10:33.470 --> 00:10:35.030 align:middle line:90%
when you come up from there.

00:10:35.030 --> 00:10:36.830 align:middle line:84%
It's really a kind
of wall marking

00:10:36.830 --> 00:10:38.600 align:middle line:84%
the start of the
land, where there's

00:10:38.600 --> 00:10:40.811 align:middle line:84%
a great number of
these standing stones.

