This, we call the Woman Stone.

00:32:36.620 --> 00:32:42.560 align:middle line:84%
From inside, this one we
refer to as the male stone

00:32:42.560 --> 00:32:44.260 align:middle line:84%
because it's obviously
very phallic.

00:32:44.260 --> 00:32:46.450 align:middle line:84%
The female stone
and the male stone

00:32:46.450 --> 00:32:51.320 align:middle line:84%
work together to form a box,
those shelves there from a box,

00:32:51.320 --> 00:32:55.190 align:middle line:84%
where the midsummer sunrise,
just after it, shines

00:32:55.190 --> 00:32:57.540 align:middle line:90%
a beam of light to this stone.

00:32:57.540 --> 00:33:01.520 align:middle line:84%
It's bringing the adages
of the sun into the ring.

00:33:01.520 --> 00:33:06.360 align:middle line:90%


00:33:06.360 --> 00:33:09.080 align:middle line:84%
>> Lost in the middle of the
Scottish lochs and heaths,

00:33:09.080 --> 00:33:11.940 align:middle line:84%
the site has a rare
strength and poetic quality.

00:33:11.940 --> 00:33:15.494 align:middle line:84%
It can't help inspiring artists
and firing the imagination.

00:33:15.494 --> 00:33:19.450 align:middle line:90%


00:33:19.450 --> 00:33:22.560 align:middle line:84%
Roger crisscrosses the
site and allows inspiration

00:33:22.560 --> 00:33:25.430 align:middle line:90%
to carry him away.

00:33:25.430 --> 00:33:28.320 align:middle line:84%
>> There would be the point,
that box, the equinox,

00:33:28.320 --> 00:33:31.540 align:middle line:84%
it echoes the shape of the
landscape, that ridge there,

00:33:31.540 --> 00:33:33.090 align:middle line:90%
that notch.

00:33:33.090 --> 00:33:35.187 align:middle line:84%
That's where the
midwinter sun sets.

00:33:35.187 --> 00:33:37.020 align:middle line:84%
Because you would
actually go like that when

00:33:37.020 --> 00:33:40.360 align:middle line:84%
something's dazzling you,
yeah, to sort of stop it

00:33:40.360 --> 00:33:41.780 align:middle line:90%
from dazzling you.

00:33:41.780 --> 00:33:46.200 align:middle line:84%
And I think they made that
stone deliberately to hide it,

00:33:46.200 --> 00:33:48.420 align:middle line:84%
because it was
hurting their eyes.

00:33:48.420 --> 00:33:50.860 align:middle line:84%
This stone, I think,
represents revering

00:33:50.860 --> 00:33:54.430 align:middle line:84%
the dead, because it seems
like a skeleton, yeah?

00:33:54.430 --> 00:33:57.120 align:middle line:84%
So it's like revering the
dead near the cairn here.

00:33:57.120 --> 00:33:59.400 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps why the later
people built the cairn

00:33:59.400 --> 00:34:03.060 align:middle line:84%
here because of this
stone with this image on.

00:34:03.060 --> 00:34:05.010 align:middle line:84%
The big stone in the
center, some people

00:34:05.010 --> 00:34:08.460 align:middle line:84%
have suggested it's
like a rudder of a boat,

00:34:08.460 --> 00:34:10.380 align:middle line:84%
you know, the steering
part of a boat,

00:34:10.380 --> 00:34:12.830 align:middle line:84%
to steer the spirits of
the dead to the stars.

00:34:12.830 --> 00:34:17.540 align:middle line:90%


00:34:17.540 --> 00:34:19.790 align:middle line:84%
>> The Callanish,
which affects us today,

00:34:19.790 --> 00:34:22.070 align:middle line:84%
is the work of people who
have mastered the cycle

00:34:22.070 --> 00:34:24.469 align:middle line:84%
of the seasons,
observed the stars,

00:34:24.469 --> 00:34:27.280 align:middle line:90%
and voyaged on the ocean.

00:34:27.280 --> 00:34:29.650 align:middle line:84%
Could these stones standing
on the hills of Scotland

00:34:29.650 --> 00:34:34.211 align:middle line:84%
be simply the symbol of a
megalithic civilization?

00:34:34.211 --> 00:34:37.080 align:middle line:84%
>> This stone circle here
is just part of the Atlantic

00:34:37.080 --> 00:34:39.510 align:middle line:84%
tradition, which you will
have links all the way down

00:34:39.510 --> 00:34:40.604 align:middle line:90%
the Atlantic coast.

00:34:40.604 --> 00:34:43.020 align:middle line:84%
There's lots of evidence to
suggest that people are moving

00:34:43.020 --> 00:34:44.728 align:middle line:84%
up and down the Atlantic
seaways but also

00:34:44.728 --> 00:34:46.529 align:middle line:90%
ideas and traditions as well.

00:34:46.529 --> 00:34:50.790 align:middle line:90%


00:34:50.790 --> 00:34:53.040 align:middle line:84%
>> Some thousands of
kilometers to the south,

00:34:53.040 --> 00:34:56.281 align:middle line:84%
like an echo to Callanish,
silhouettes of stones are lost

00:34:56.281 --> 00:34:57.081 align:middle line:90%
in the sea.

00:34:57.081 --> 00:34:59.850 align:middle line:90%


00:34:59.850 --> 00:35:03.420 align:middle line:84%
Witness to the changes in the
landscape over 5,000 years,

00:35:03.420 --> 00:35:07.800 align:middle line:84%
these half-drowned arcs of
standing stones intrigue us.

00:35:07.800 --> 00:35:11.110 align:middle line:84%
Sited in the Gulf of Morbihan,
the island of Er Lannic

00:35:11.110 --> 00:35:13.090 align:middle line:84%
has been declared
a natural reserve.

00:35:13.090 --> 00:35:15.070 align:middle line:84%
It is only accessible
by sea, and it

00:35:15.070 --> 00:35:17.950 align:middle line:90%
is forbidden to set foot there.

00:35:17.950 --> 00:35:19.970 align:middle line:84%
So Laurent Lescop is
taken there in a boat

00:35:19.970 --> 00:35:22.506 align:middle line:84%
by Yves Belenfant, who
knows the place well.

00:35:22.506 --> 00:35:26.790 align:middle line:90%


00:35:26.790 --> 00:35:29.180 align:middle line:84%
>> It's a double
semi-circle really.

00:35:29.180 --> 00:35:31.740 align:middle line:84%
It's not completely
two arcs of a circle.

00:35:31.740 --> 00:35:34.170 align:middle line:84%
So there we can see the
first, and the second you

00:35:34.170 --> 00:35:36.680 align:middle line:84%
can't see, because it's
completely immersed.

00:35:36.680 --> 00:35:37.770 align:middle line:90%
Here, we're at full tide.

00:35:37.770 --> 00:35:40.105 align:middle line:84%
So at full tide, they're at
about three to four meters

00:35:40.105 --> 00:35:40.905 align:middle line:90%
maximum.

00:35:40.905 --> 00:35:44.816 align:middle line:90%


00:35:44.816 --> 00:35:48.310 align:middle line:84%
The monoliths that we see
here in the first arc,

00:35:48.310 --> 00:35:50.770 align:middle line:84%
well, there's a big one
there, the one at the summit.

00:35:50.770 --> 00:35:52.780 align:middle line:84%
But the monoliths of
the second semicircle,

00:35:52.780 --> 00:35:58.076 align:middle line:84%
which are completely immersed,
are three to four times bigger.

00:35:58.076 --> 00:36:01.004 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:36:01.004 --> 00:36:08.330 align:middle line:90%


00:36:08.330 --> 00:36:11.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Archaeological excavations
made near the stones have given

00:36:11.270 --> 00:36:12.800 align:middle line:84%
clues to the
function of the site.

00:36:12.800 --> 00:36:16.580 align:middle line:90%


00:36:16.580 --> 00:36:18.890 align:middle line:84%
>> When we look at the
archaeological material that

00:36:18.890 --> 00:36:24.110 align:middle line:84%
has been found, there's over
a ton of pottery and traces

00:36:24.110 --> 00:36:26.690 align:middle line:90%
of elements of fumigation.

00:36:26.690 --> 00:36:29.950 align:middle line:84%
So this could have links with
some kind of cult practice.

00:36:29.950 --> 00:36:35.150 align:middle line:90%


00:36:35.150 --> 00:36:39.320 align:middle line:84%
There were also a number
of little flint arrows

00:36:39.320 --> 00:36:42.920 align:middle line:84%
and as well, there were
casings, and in these casings

00:36:42.920 --> 00:36:45.620 align:middle line:90%
were the burned bones of cattle.

00:36:45.620 --> 00:36:48.260 align:middle line:84%
So we have something which
is perhaps a lot more

00:36:48.260 --> 00:36:52.310 align:middle line:84%
to do with the ceremony, cult
of some kind, but what kind,

00:36:52.310 --> 00:36:55.900 align:middle line:90%
it's very hard to say.

00:36:55.900 --> 00:36:58.690 align:middle line:84%
>> One thing is sure is that
the semi-circles of stone were

00:36:58.690 --> 00:37:01.480 align:middle line:84%
raised on dry land in a
very different landscape,

00:37:01.480 --> 00:37:03.760 align:middle line:84%
which has since been altered
by the change in climate.

00:37:03.760 --> 00:37:07.990 align:middle line:90%


00:37:07.990 --> 00:37:10.550 align:middle line:84%
Laurent has made a
photographic survey of the site

00:37:10.550 --> 00:37:16.510 align:middle line:84%
to model it in 3D and simulate
the original environment.

00:37:16.510 --> 00:37:19.630 align:middle line:84%
5,000 years ago, it's
estimated the water level

00:37:19.630 --> 00:37:22.810 align:middle line:90%
was six to eight meters lower.

00:37:22.810 --> 00:37:26.260 align:middle line:10%
>> It's true that imagining this
place without water requires

00:37:26.260 --> 00:37:28.450 align:middle line:10%
a little effort of
the imagination.

00:37:28.450 --> 00:37:31.670 align:middle line:10%
So this image will help
that effort of imagination.

00:37:31.670 --> 00:37:33.670 align:middle line:84%
It's a model which
will help to understand

00:37:33.670 --> 00:37:36.568 align:middle line:84%
the proportions of this to
the scale of the landscape.

00:37:36.568 --> 00:37:40.060 align:middle line:90%


00:37:40.060 --> 00:37:42.850 align:middle line:84%
>> These standing stones were
without doubt part of a group

00:37:42.850 --> 00:37:45.280 align:middle line:90%
of interconnected sites.

00:37:45.280 --> 00:37:47.950 align:middle line:84%
In fact, far off, on the
other side of the sea,

00:37:47.950 --> 00:37:49.750 align:middle line:84%
is a construction
of dry stones, which

00:37:49.750 --> 00:37:51.130 align:middle line:90%
the archeologists call a cairn.

00:37:51.130 --> 00:37:56.920 align:middle line:90%


00:37:56.920 --> 00:37:59.740 align:middle line:84%
The Cairn of Gavrinis
is a funerary monument

00:37:59.740 --> 00:38:02.320 align:middle line:90%
built around 4000 years BC.

00:38:02.320 --> 00:38:04.807 align:middle line:84%
Beneath this massive stone
is hidden a treasure,

00:38:04.807 --> 00:38:07.140 align:middle line:84%
and this is one of the sites
explored by Laurent Lescop.

00:38:07.140 --> 00:38:12.220 align:middle line:90%


00:38:12.220 --> 00:38:14.790 align:middle line:84%
22 of the 24 blocks
of stone which

00:38:14.790 --> 00:38:17.100 align:middle line:84%
make up the inner corridor
and funeral chamber

00:38:17.100 --> 00:38:19.320 align:middle line:84%
are entirely
covered in carvings.

00:38:19.320 --> 00:38:22.200 align:middle line:10%
The site is known for this
reason as the Neolithic Sistine

00:38:22.200 --> 00:38:23.000 align:middle line:10%
Chapel.

00:38:23.000 --> 00:38:25.390 align:middle line:90%


00:38:25.390 --> 00:38:27.950 align:middle line:84%
Laurent is carefully
surveying all the stones

00:38:27.950 --> 00:38:30.890 align:middle line:84%
to model them in 3D and thus,
be able to better decipher

00:38:30.890 --> 00:38:33.220 align:middle line:90%
the motifs.

00:38:33.220 --> 00:38:35.530 align:middle line:84%
>> We can see the carvings
much more precisely.

00:38:35.530 --> 00:38:40.600 align:middle line:90%


00:38:40.600 --> 00:38:42.760 align:middle line:84%
One very important
element is the position

00:38:42.760 --> 00:38:45.820 align:middle line:84%
of each carving within
the global space.

00:38:45.820 --> 00:38:48.340 align:middle line:84%
That is to say, until now,
what we had been seeing

00:38:48.340 --> 00:38:51.770 align:middle line:84%
were carvings
reproduced on a plan.

00:38:51.770 --> 00:38:53.800 align:middle line:84%
So we had little idea
of the volume over which

00:38:53.800 --> 00:38:56.920 align:middle line:90%
the carvings stretched.

00:38:56.920 --> 00:39:02.080 align:middle line:10%
However, Gavrinis by closely
observing all of the stones,

00:39:02.080 --> 00:39:04.000 align:middle line:10%
we see that some
carvings are directed

00:39:04.000 --> 00:39:07.570 align:middle line:10%
by the volume of the stones,
by the starting model

00:39:07.570 --> 00:39:08.590 align:middle line:10%
that the stone offered.

00:39:08.590 --> 00:39:14.400 align:middle line:90%


00:39:14.400 --> 00:39:16.590 align:middle line:84%
Given the density,
the regularity

00:39:16.590 --> 00:39:18.840 align:middle line:84%
and the way in which
things have been done,

00:39:18.840 --> 00:39:21.240 align:middle line:84%
we can ask ourselves if
it was the same hand which

00:39:21.240 --> 00:39:24.340 align:middle line:84%
carved the whole site,
and in that case,

00:39:24.340 --> 00:39:26.905 align:middle line:84%
we would have ourselves here
a Michelangelo of that time.

00:39:26.905 --> 00:39:31.140 align:middle line:90%


00:39:31.140 --> 00:39:34.260 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the remarkable
elements is found here.

00:39:34.260 --> 00:39:35.440 align:middle line:90%
These are, in fact, boats.

00:39:35.440 --> 00:39:36.900 align:middle line:90%
They are here and there.

00:39:36.900 --> 00:39:39.780 align:middle line:84%
And then these elements, like
points, would be the crew.

00:39:39.780 --> 00:39:42.180 align:middle line:84%
It's a way of representing
the boats and their crews that

00:39:42.180 --> 00:39:44.370 align:middle line:84%
is found in a lot of
carvings of this time.

00:39:44.370 --> 00:39:49.080 align:middle line:90%


00:39:49.080 --> 00:39:51.330 align:middle line:84%
>> The maritime environment
certainly influenced

00:39:51.330 --> 00:39:53.817 align:middle line:84%
the artistic repertory of
the Neolithic occupants

00:39:53.817 --> 00:39:54.617 align:middle line:90%
of the region.

00:39:54.617 --> 00:39:57.990 align:middle line:90%


00:39:57.990 --> 00:40:02.140 align:middle line:84%
>> When you see the current,
you can see it makes arcs,

00:40:02.140 --> 00:40:05.230 align:middle line:84%
and you could ask yourself if
these forms inspired what we

00:40:05.230 --> 00:40:06.070 align:middle line:90%
find inside.

00:40:06.070 --> 00:40:13.810 align:middle line:90%


00:40:13.810 --> 00:40:17.050 align:middle line:84%
>> Laurent's objective is also
to make a precise 3D model

00:40:17.050 --> 00:40:18.280 align:middle line:90%
of the exterior of the site.

00:40:18.280 --> 00:40:21.577 align:middle line:90%


00:40:21.577 --> 00:40:24.780 align:middle line:10%
>> Here, for example, we have
the general volume of the cairn

00:40:24.780 --> 00:40:27.780 align:middle line:10%
as a scatter plot, and you can
see there are some elements

00:40:27.780 --> 00:40:31.410 align:middle line:10%
missing, which will probably be
completed by the shots we take

00:40:31.410 --> 00:40:32.210 align:middle line:10%
with the drone.

00:40:32.210 --> 00:40:37.210 align:middle line:90%


00:40:37.210 --> 00:40:39.070 align:middle line:84%
With the images
taken by the drone,

00:40:39.070 --> 00:40:41.590 align:middle line:84%
I'll be able to have the
whole of the site all at once

00:40:41.590 --> 00:40:45.980 align:middle line:84%
with a lot of detail, which will
then come in very, very useful.

00:40:45.980 --> 00:40:47.080 align:middle line:90%
>> OK, we'll take off.

00:40:47.080 --> 00:40:53.380 align:middle line:90%


00:40:53.380 --> 00:40:55.720 align:middle line:90%
Can we sweep the facade there?

00:40:55.720 --> 00:40:56.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, of course.

00:40:56.710 --> 00:40:58.440 align:middle line:90%
We'll go from left to right.

00:40:58.440 --> 00:41:10.140 align:middle line:90%
>> There, that's perfect

00:41:10.140 --> 00:41:12.840 align:middle line:84%
>> The use of models for the
exterior is to get the complete

00:41:12.840 --> 00:41:16.460 align:middle line:84%
volume and the interior to have
detail of all the carvings,

00:41:16.460 --> 00:41:18.810 align:middle line:84%
to relate the inside
to the outside,

00:41:18.810 --> 00:41:21.180 align:middle line:84%
allowing us to place the
corridor very precisely

00:41:21.180 --> 00:41:24.530 align:middle line:84%
in the cairn and have an image,
a bit like an ultrasound image.

00:41:24.530 --> 00:41:27.620 align:middle line:90%


00:41:27.620 --> 00:41:30.450 align:middle line:84%
>> Laurent thinks that
the corridor of the Cairn

00:41:30.450 --> 00:41:33.770 align:middle line:84%
of Gavrinis was lined up in
relation to the axis of the sun

00:41:33.770 --> 00:41:36.170 align:middle line:90%
at the winter solstice.

00:41:36.170 --> 00:41:39.160 align:middle line:84%
On the 21st of December,
the first rays of the sun

00:41:39.160 --> 00:41:47.680 align:middle line:84%
light up the corridor
in the funeral chamber,

00:41:47.680 --> 00:41:49.660 align:middle line:84%
one more sign that
shows the close link

00:41:49.660 --> 00:41:51.490 align:middle line:84%
for Neolithic people
between nature

00:41:51.490 --> 00:41:53.190 align:middle line:84%
and all the forces
that drive it.

00:41:53.190 --> 00:42:02.820 align:middle line:90%


00:42:02.820 --> 00:42:06.130 align:middle line:84%
>> Natural elements, whether
they be stone, water, wind,

00:42:06.130 --> 00:42:09.560 align:middle line:84%
or the stars have contributed to
the placing of these megaliths.

00:42:09.560 --> 00:42:12.560 align:middle line:90%


00:42:12.560 --> 00:42:15.380 align:middle line:84%
>> This proximity between
standing stones and natural

00:42:15.380 --> 00:42:18.105 align:middle line:84%
forces has helped to feed many
beliefs and legends throughout

00:42:18.105 --> 00:42:18.905 align:middle line:90%
the ages.

00:42:18.905 --> 00:42:22.580 align:middle line:90%


00:42:22.580 --> 00:42:25.660 align:middle line:10%
>> There are several legends
linked to the Giant Gargantua,

00:42:25.660 --> 00:42:29.750 align:middle line:10%
to the fairies, to the
Corrigans, or Brittany elves.

00:42:29.750 --> 00:42:31.610 align:middle line:10%
For example, the
Giant Gargantua,

00:42:31.610 --> 00:42:34.180 align:middle line:10%
who often had a pebble in
his shoes, pulled it out,

00:42:34.180 --> 00:42:37.360 align:middle line:10%
and when it fell
it became a menhir.

00:42:37.360 --> 00:42:41.270 align:middle line:84%
Or it's said that the spindle
of a fairy spinning wheel

00:42:41.270 --> 00:42:44.170 align:middle line:90%
was turned into a menhir.

00:42:44.170 --> 00:42:48.200 align:middle line:84%
Or that the dolmen were the
houses of the Corrigans,

00:42:48.200 --> 00:42:51.860 align:middle line:84%
those mischief elves,
that once night fell

00:42:51.860 --> 00:42:55.550 align:middle line:84%
could lead you into
infernal dances,

00:42:55.550 --> 00:42:57.020 align:middle line:90%
and you'd never be seen again.

00:42:57.020 --> 00:43:02.330 align:middle line:90%


00:43:02.330 --> 00:43:04.640 align:middle line:84%
Very close to
megalithic monuments

00:43:04.640 --> 00:43:07.340 align:middle line:84%
are often found natural
outcrops of rock

00:43:07.340 --> 00:43:09.680 align:middle line:84%
on the surface
formed geologically

00:43:09.680 --> 00:43:12.620 align:middle line:90%
by natural erosion of granite.

00:43:12.620 --> 00:43:14.360 align:middle line:84%
And these rocks,
which were often

00:43:14.360 --> 00:43:16.580 align:middle line:84%
thought to be
sacrificial stones,

00:43:16.580 --> 00:43:17.670 align:middle line:90%
have led to many legends.

00:43:17.670 --> 00:43:23.000 align:middle line:90%


00:43:23.000 --> 00:43:25.010 align:middle line:84%
Some menhirs were used
for fertility rights

00:43:25.010 --> 00:43:26.540 align:middle line:90%
for women wanting children.

00:43:26.540 --> 00:43:29.480 align:middle line:10%
Small flowers braided with oil
were brought to the menhir,

00:43:29.480 --> 00:43:31.550 align:middle line:10%
and they rub their stomachs
against the menhir,

00:43:31.550 --> 00:43:35.420 align:middle line:10%
naked preferably, and I've seen
this done, not by new agers

00:43:35.420 --> 00:43:37.200 align:middle line:10%
but by older folk.

00:43:37.200 --> 00:43:39.650 align:middle line:84%
So it hasn't yet disappeared
from tradition here.

00:43:39.650 --> 00:43:42.950 align:middle line:84%
It brings us back again to the
idea of a force in the stone.

00:43:42.950 --> 00:43:44.840 align:middle line:84%
When you see a
standing stone, I don't

00:43:44.840 --> 00:43:47.240 align:middle line:84%
want to be a total
Freudian, and I'm not one,

00:43:47.240 --> 00:43:49.250 align:middle line:84%
but there is a phallic
quality all the same

00:43:49.250 --> 00:43:51.030 align:middle line:84%
in these enormous
standing stones,

00:43:51.030 --> 00:43:53.150 align:middle line:84%
